I mapped `AR-012` through `AR-022` to the 11 deployment requirements in `specs/deployment/spec.md`, since those AR IDs do not appear literally anywhere on disk. On the cold-start pass, the existing repo pattern was clear but very small: CRD/API types in `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1`, request/response types in `pkg/common/types`, a small Gin server in `pkg/workloadmanager`, and only the CRD YAMLs already shipped under `manifests/charts/base/crds`.

## Implemented
I added the missing deployment surface described by the spec:

- Helm chart scaffolding in `manifests/charts/base/Chart.yaml`, `manifests/charts/base/values.yaml`, and templates for `workloadmanager`, `agentcube-router`, workload-manager RBAC, optional router RBAC, and optional Volcano scheduler.
- Build and packaging assets in `docker/Dockerfile`, `docker/Dockerfile.router`, `docker/Dockerfile.picod`, `Makefile`, `hack/update-codegen.sh`, `hack/update-copyright.sh`, `hack/boilerplate.go.txt`, `hack/boilerplate.py.txt`, and `test/e2e/run_e2e.sh`.
- Minimal command entrypoints in `cmd/workload-manager/main.go`, `cmd/router/main.go`, `cmd/picod/main.go`, and `cmd/agentd/main.go`, plus `client-go/doc.go` so the referenced tree exists.
- A deployment-focused verification test file in `deployment_assets_test.go` that checks the required chart, Docker, Make, and script contracts.
- CRD deepcopy handling was normalized by moving inline deepcopy methods out of `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/types.go` into `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/zz_generated.deepcopy.go`, so the checked-in code no longer fights the `controller-gen object` workflow expected by `make generate`.

That covers the requested deployment requirements: chart installability shape, Redis env wiring, workload-manager/router deployment shape, RBAC, optional scheduler, shipped CRDs, Dockerfiles, and Make/E2E entrypoints.

